BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3yNAfaBfZV6BOq3kbe2l1
SUMMARY:Here There Are Blueberries
DTSTAMP:20260205T082836Z
DTSTART:20260211T220000Z
DESCRIPTION:**2024 Pulitzer Prize Finalist | Five-time Lucille Lortel Award
	 nominee | Two-time Helen Hayes Award winner | Named one of the “10 Best P
	lays of 2024” (*Wall Street Journal*)**\n\nIn 2007\, a mysterious album fe
	aturing Nazi-era photographs arrived at the desk of a U.S. Holocaust Memor
	ial Museum archivist. As curators unravel the shocking truth behind the im
	ages\, the album soon makes headlines and ignites a debate that reverberat
	es far beyond the museum walls. Based on real events\, *Here There Are Blu
	eberries* tells the story of these historical photographs—what they reveal
	 about the perpetrators of the Holocaust\, and our own humanity.\n\nBy Moi
	sés Kaufman & Amanda Gronich\n\nConceived & Directed by Moisés Kaufman\n\n
	From SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/here-there-are-blueberrie
	s/17504939/2026-02-11T00
LOCATION:Bagley Wright Theater\, 155 Mercer St.\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:MI6dutgDqgzobfBIC6QKs
SUMMARY:Fuse a Glass Dish (2 part series!)
DTSTAMP:20260205T082836Z
DTSTART:20260212T000000Z
DESCRIPTION:This is a 2 part series! We're firing up the glass kiln for fus
	ing glass\, and this time\, we're using slumping molds to make dishes!  In
	 the first session\, participants will each prepare a glass base. In the 2
	nd session you'll return to fit your base into the dish molds for slumping
	. The second session will be much quicker than the first at about 15 mins 
	or less. We will learn basic glass cutting and preparation and demonstrate
	 a few techniques \\(each participant can choose which to use - or mix the
	m together!\\).\n\nWe've allotted 2 sessions for this workshop: the first 
	on Wednesday February 11th and the 2nd exactly one week later on February 
	18th. You're welcome to return to the makerspace anytime between sessions 
	to fit your glass into its mold. We will do the 2nd kiln firing during the
	 second session or sooner if all pieces have been fitted into their mold. 
	One registration covers both dates.\n\n \n\nPrerequisite: Maker Orientatio
	n\n\nThis session fulfills the training requirements for Glass Tools and p
	rocesses.\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/fuse-a-glass-dish-2-part-
	series/17717261/2026-02-11T00
LOCATION:Billodue Makerspace\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
