SUMMARY:SafeCampus Violence Prevention and Response Training
DTSTAMP:20260205T082836Z
DTSTART:20260218T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Wednesday\, Feb 18\, 2026\, 9:30 - 11 a.m. PST\n\nDuring this i
	nteractive training\, we ask participants to consider their unique role in
	 preventing violence at the University of Washington. This training has be
	en adapted to consider the remote academic environments that many staff\, 
	students\, and faculty are currently experiencing. We will explore mental 
	health and warning signs of different forms of violence including\; workpl
	ace violence\, relationship violence\, sexual harassment\, and stalking. W
	e will briefly practice in-person and remote bystander intervention techni
	ques and build your understanding of UW resources.\n\nClick the link below
	 to register for this training.\n\nCampus room: Online Zoom Training Acces
